1
00:02:13,910 --> 00:02:15,790
Run for Young

2
00:02:16,990 --> 00:02:17,750
Hurry up.

3
00:02:17,830 --> 00:02:19,430
Doggo hasn't had noodles. He's starving.

4
00:02:19,830 --> 00:02:20,350
Go get some.

5
00:02:20,350 --> 00:02:22,110
I heard you. Stop pushing.

6
00:02:24,270 --> 00:02:24,870
Up.

7
00:02:27,350 --> 00:02:27,970
Wait.

8
00:02:28,070 --> 00:02:28,690
Money.

9
00:02:28,870 --> 00:02:29,470
Here.

10
00:02:29,470 --> 00:02:30,110
Here.

11
00:02:30,110 --> 00:02:30,590
Well, well.

12
00:02:30,590 --> 00:02:31,190
Got it?

13
00:02:31,190 --> 00:02:31,870
Yeah.

14
00:02:32,790 --> 00:02:34,190
Someone just tipped me off

15
00:02:34,190 --> 00:02:35,550
that someone is skipping school.

16
00:02:36,230 --> 00:02:37,390
So, it's you!

17
00:02:37,590 --> 00:02:38,470
Ding Rongliang!

18
00:02:38,950 --> 00:02:39,750
I'm not.

19
00:02:40,430 --> 00:02:41,870
Then why are you sneaking around?

20
00:02:47,830 --> 00:02:48,510
FOR ENCOUNTERS

21
00:02:50,109 --> 00:02:51,230
During an encounter,

22
00:02:51,549 --> 00:02:52,710
act uninhibited.

23
00:02:52,990 --> 00:02:54,270
Don't panic.

24
00:02:54,430 --> 00:02:55,990
Singing would be preferable.

25
00:02:59,870 --> 00:03:01,190
Why are you being sneaky?

26
00:03:03,230 --> 00:03:04,310
I'll call Director Pan!

27
00:03:04,670 --> 00:03:05,290
Wait.

28
00:03:07,750 --> 00:03:08,830
What's your trick now?

29
00:03:09,790 --> 00:03:13,710
♪ The girl opposite, please look over here ♪

30
00:03:13,710 --> 00:03:17,710
♪ Look over here ♪

31
00:03:18,190 --> 00:03:21,630
♪ Don't be scared by my appearance ♪

32
00:03:21,990 --> 00:03:23,390
♪ I'm actually ♪

33
00:03:23,990 --> 00:03:26,390
♪ Adorable ♪

34
00:03:27,510 --> 00:03:31,310
♪ I look left and right, look up and down ♪

35
00:03:31,870 --> 00:03:34,910
♪ It turns out that every girl is not that simple ♪

36
00:03:52,190 --> 00:03:57,190
Episode 2 Stay Foolish, Stay Together

37
00:04:10,630 --> 00:04:11,910
Marathon team, assemble.

38
00:04:18,070 --> 00:04:21,110
I'm your coach in charge of your team.

39
00:04:21,790 --> 00:04:22,430
Yes, coach.

40
00:04:26,110 --> 00:04:27,670
I'll also be responsible

41
00:04:28,550 --> 00:04:30,390
for your training.

42
00:04:30,790 --> 00:04:32,350
I'll try my best to train you.

43
00:04:34,750 --> 00:04:35,430
Now,

44
00:04:35,950 --> 00:04:37,110
your team lead will take over.

45
00:04:57,310 --> 00:04:58,670
Three laps of leapfrog first.

46
00:05:09,070 --> 00:05:09,990
Come on!

47
00:05:10,310 --> 00:05:11,470
Extra points for a better

48
00:05:11,750 --> 00:05:12,350
college!

49
00:05:12,590 --> 00:05:13,870
You don't have to do this.

50
00:05:13,870 --> 00:05:14,870
Just run normally.

51
00:05:16,950 --> 00:05:17,550
Why?

52
00:05:18,910 --> 00:05:20,230
You're old.

53
00:05:20,230 --> 00:05:20,990
Take it easy.

54
00:05:22,550 --> 00:05:23,270
Team lead,

55
00:05:23,670 --> 00:05:24,990
I actually run pretty well.

56
00:05:26,030 --> 00:05:26,950
Besides, look at them.

57
00:05:28,270 --> 00:05:29,510
I don't think they can win.

58
00:05:36,710 --> 00:05:38,070
What a crappy team!

59
00:05:38,910 --> 00:05:40,350
The coach in charge

60
00:05:41,030 --> 00:05:42,750
just doesn't care.

61
00:05:43,190 --> 00:05:45,630
And the team lead is taking revenge for private grudge.

62
00:06:00,390 --> 00:06:01,310
Don't you think

63
00:06:01,310 --> 00:06:02,470
you're crossing the line?

64
00:06:04,110 --> 00:06:05,630
Did you forget how I got into the team?

65
00:06:10,630 --> 00:06:11,590
Are you tired?

66
00:06:15,230 --> 00:06:16,510
You two can rest.

67
00:06:16,750 --> 00:06:17,470
What about Doggo?

68
00:06:18,990 --> 00:06:20,070
And you?

69
00:06:20,070 --> 00:06:20,790
Are you tired?

70
00:06:22,150 --> 00:06:22,950
You can rest.

71
00:06:24,390 --> 00:06:25,110
No way!

72
00:06:25,390 --> 00:06:26,310
Why not?

73
00:06:26,550 --> 00:06:27,830
Because we're friends!

74
00:06:31,430 --> 00:06:32,550
That's it for today.

75
00:06:33,270 --> 00:06:34,070
Tell them to stop.

76
00:06:35,510 --> 00:06:36,470
All right. Stop.

77
00:06:36,470 --> 00:06:37,430
He said, "Stop."

78
00:06:37,430 --> 00:06:39,110
You'll become frogs if you go on.

79
00:06:39,110 --> 00:06:40,190
Get up.

80
00:06:40,190 --> 00:06:41,590
That's enough. For real.

81
00:06:51,830 --> 00:06:52,830
Pick it up.

82
00:06:53,550 --> 00:06:54,150
Why?

83
00:06:54,430 --> 00:06:56,430
You are only the team lead when we're training.

84
00:07:02,750 --> 00:07:04,390
At least be moderate when taking revenge.

85
00:07:04,430 --> 00:07:06,070
Who got me into the team?

86
00:07:06,070 --> 00:07:07,310
I did. So what?

87
00:07:07,790 --> 00:07:08,750
Why did you do that?

88
00:07:09,390 --> 00:07:10,790
None of your business.

89
00:07:10,790 --> 00:07:11,750
Sure it is.

90
00:07:12,070 --> 00:07:12,710
Screw you!

91
00:07:12,990 --> 00:07:13,590
What?

92
00:07:14,110 --> 00:07:14,910
I'll kick you.

93
00:07:15,110 --> 00:07:16,470
Who gave you the right?

94
00:07:16,590 --> 00:07:17,350
You want a fight?

95
00:07:17,550 --> 00:07:18,190
I'll hit your dad.

96
00:07:19,310 --> 00:07:19,950
Your dad.

97
00:07:19,950 --> 00:07:20,950
Me too.

98
00:07:20,950 --> 00:07:21,590
Your dad.

99
00:07:21,590 --> 00:07:22,590
I'm hitting your grandpa.

100
00:07:22,590 --> 00:07:23,590
Your grandpa.

101
00:07:23,590 --> 00:07:24,350
Your dad.

102
00:07:25,110 --> 00:07:25,670
Say it again!

103
00:07:25,870 --> 00:07:26,470
What?

104
00:07:26,550 --> 00:07:27,150
Say it again!

105
00:07:27,190 --> 00:07:27,790
Ma Tian, let go.

106
00:07:28,870 --> 00:07:29,670
Punch him!

107
00:07:29,670 --> 00:07:30,110
Say it again!

108
00:07:30,110 --> 00:07:30,730
Doggo!

109
00:07:31,070 --> 00:07:31,670
Forget it.

110
00:07:31,670 --> 00:07:32,430
Let go!

111
00:07:37,870 --> 00:07:39,710
Why don't you sweep it into the dustpan?

112
00:07:40,470 --> 00:07:41,950
Why don't you do it?

113
00:07:43,030 --> 00:07:44,030
You do it.

114
00:07:44,110 --> 00:07:45,110
You do it.

115
00:07:45,710 --> 00:07:47,070
You do it.

116
00:07:47,590 --> 00:07:48,790
You do it.

117
00:07:48,990 --> 00:07:49,750
You do it.

118
00:07:49,910 --> 00:07:50,710
You do it.

119
00:07:50,790 --> 00:07:51,790
You do it.

120
00:07:51,790 --> 00:07:52,950
Are you done?

121
00:07:57,630 --> 00:07:58,830
If our brother were here,

122
00:07:58,830 --> 00:08:00,630
you wouldn't be so arrogant.

123
00:08:01,190 --> 00:08:02,190
Which brother?

124
00:08:02,190 --> 00:08:03,630
Liu Wenqin. Qin.

125
00:08:04,070 --> 00:08:05,110
Qin!

126
00:08:05,110 --> 00:08:06,550
What a shame! He's not at school.

127
00:08:06,550 --> 00:08:07,670
Scared, huh?

128
00:08:07,670 --> 00:08:09,310
Why don't we find him?

129
00:08:09,310 --> 00:08:10,110
He will be back.

130
00:08:10,110 --> 00:08:11,710
He will crush you, pretty face!

131
00:08:11,710 --> 00:08:12,310
Crush you!

132
00:08:13,150 --> 00:08:13,990
He'll crush you!

133
00:08:14,910 --> 00:08:15,510
Let's go.

134
00:08:16,150 --> 00:08:16,910
Clean it up.

135
00:08:18,950 --> 00:08:20,350
Let's go. Ignore them.

136
00:08:20,790 --> 00:08:21,410
Let's go.

137
00:08:23,390 --> 00:08:24,430
My buddies.

138
00:08:24,430 --> 00:08:25,030
Let's go.

139
00:08:25,110 --> 00:08:25,750
Let's go.

140
00:08:37,470 --> 00:08:38,550
Attention please.

141
00:08:39,510 --> 00:08:40,710
During your senior year,

142
00:08:40,710 --> 00:08:41,710
we plan to set up some

143
00:08:41,710 --> 00:08:43,030
one-to-one revision groups

144
00:08:43,150 --> 00:08:43,870
for three purposes.

145
00:08:44,470 --> 00:08:46,270
First, the good students

146
00:08:46,270 --> 00:08:47,390
can review the books

147
00:08:47,390 --> 00:08:48,350
while helping others.

148
00:08:49,070 --> 00:08:50,590
Second, the underachieving ones

149
00:08:50,590 --> 00:08:51,430
will get help.

150
00:08:52,070 --> 00:08:53,510
Third, let's boost the admission rate

151
00:08:53,510 --> 00:08:54,270
to college.

152
00:08:55,830 --> 00:08:56,950
First,

153
00:08:59,030 --> 00:08:59,750
Tu Jun.

154
00:09:01,270 --> 00:09:02,430
Who would like to help him?

155
00:09:08,190 --> 00:09:08,790
Me.

156
00:09:09,990 --> 00:09:10,590
Me.

157
00:09:10,750 --> 00:09:11,830
Teaty, what are you doing?

158
00:09:11,830 --> 00:09:12,830
Put your hand down.

159
00:09:12,830 --> 00:09:13,710
Mind your business.

160
00:09:13,790 --> 00:09:14,430
Teaty,

161
00:09:14,430 --> 00:09:15,270
how can you help?

162
00:09:15,310 --> 00:09:16,989
Who is willing to help Tu Jun?

163
00:09:21,350 --> 00:09:22,629
Anyone?

164
00:09:24,510 --> 00:09:25,670
Miss, I will help him.

165
00:09:32,030 --> 00:09:33,390
What? Any objections?

166
00:09:33,470 --> 00:09:34,230
I need help, too.

167
00:09:35,390 --> 00:09:37,070
You already have Ma Tian next to you.

168
00:09:37,070 --> 00:09:38,470
Who else do you need?

169
00:09:43,230 --> 00:09:44,150
Jiao, what's wrong?

170
00:09:44,150 --> 00:09:44,770
Get lost.

171
00:09:47,030 --> 00:09:48,310
Miss, I disagree.

172
00:09:48,830 --> 00:09:49,710
What is it now?

173
00:09:49,910 --> 00:09:51,670
I think she's up to something.

174
00:09:51,670 --> 00:09:52,670
It will affect me.

175
00:10:25,270 --> 00:10:26,270
I said no.

176
00:10:29,670 --> 00:10:30,910
You made me do it.

177
00:10:35,470 --> 00:10:36,550
I'll jump if you stay.

178
00:10:36,550 --> 00:10:37,170
Jump.

179
00:10:51,530 --> 00:10:52,150
Please.

180
00:10:52,150 --> 00:10:52,950
You are so young.

181
00:10:52,950 --> 00:10:53,990
Don't die, please.

182
00:10:58,150 --> 00:10:59,270
You all heard her.

183
00:10:59,270 --> 00:11:00,350
She begged me.

184
00:11:08,950 --> 00:11:10,110
Whatever you say.

185
00:11:13,870 --> 00:11:14,550
Hercules Jiao,

186
00:11:14,550 --> 00:11:15,270
look.

187
00:11:15,350 --> 00:11:16,230
The new girl

188
00:11:16,230 --> 00:11:17,230
must be into me.

189
00:11:17,670 --> 00:11:18,910
I was just testing her.

190
00:11:18,910 --> 00:11:19,910
I said I would jump

191
00:11:19,910 --> 00:11:21,230
and she just begged me.

192
00:11:22,470 --> 00:11:23,910
She was so afraid of losing me.

193
00:11:24,390 --> 00:11:25,310
But,

194
00:11:25,310 --> 00:11:27,310
she and Ma Tian are good friends.

195
00:11:27,310 --> 00:11:28,830
She's struggling, too.

196
00:11:28,830 --> 00:11:30,670
On the one hand, it's the boy she likes.

197
00:11:30,670 --> 00:11:32,390
On the other hand, it's her good friend.

198
00:11:32,510 --> 00:11:33,830
Who would you choose?

199
00:11:35,510 --> 00:11:36,150
It's too hard.

200
00:11:37,110 --> 00:11:38,110
But don't worry, Hercules Jiao.

201
00:11:39,670 --> 00:11:40,790
We are buddies.

202
00:11:40,790 --> 00:11:41,670
How can I like

203
00:11:41,670 --> 00:11:42,870
the girl you don't like?

204
00:11:46,510 --> 00:11:47,150
Hercules Jiao,

205
00:11:47,150 --> 00:11:48,790
don't pull a long face.

206
00:11:48,790 --> 00:11:50,630
Friends are all about brotherhood.

207
00:11:50,790 --> 00:11:51,630
I, Tu Jun,

208
00:11:51,630 --> 00:11:52,990
will never betray you.

209
00:12:09,550 --> 00:12:10,390
I know.

210
00:12:10,590 --> 00:12:12,350
You're with Ma Tian

211
00:12:12,470 --> 00:12:14,030
to embarrass me.

212
00:12:14,030 --> 00:12:15,350
In your dreams.

213
00:12:15,750 --> 00:12:16,550
Tell you what.

214
00:12:16,830 --> 00:12:17,950
I just won't listen.

215
00:12:17,950 --> 00:12:18,950
I just won't study.

216
00:12:18,950 --> 00:12:20,310
What can you do to me?

217
00:12:23,750 --> 00:12:24,370
Tell you what.

218
00:12:24,990 --> 00:12:25,950
Dozens of people

219
00:12:26,270 --> 00:12:28,750
in this class tried to help me with my studies.

220
00:12:29,190 --> 00:12:30,750
That was just impossible.

221
00:12:30,750 --> 00:12:31,630
Do you know why?

222
00:12:31,630 --> 00:12:32,510
Because

223
00:12:32,510 --> 00:12:34,350
a dead mouse feels no cold.

224
00:12:51,190 --> 00:12:52,310
Tell you what.

225
00:12:52,550 --> 00:12:54,230
Girls like you

226
00:12:54,230 --> 00:12:56,190
cover yourself up so well.

227
00:12:56,830 --> 00:12:58,070
So serious. So righteous.

228
00:12:58,310 --> 00:12:59,830
Not interesting at all.

229
00:13:00,790 --> 00:13:02,470
A playboy like me

230
00:13:02,470 --> 00:13:04,350
won't fall for a girl like you.

231
00:13:07,870 --> 00:13:08,630
Put it this way...

232
00:13:08,630 --> 00:13:09,870
Doggo,

233
00:13:09,870 --> 00:13:11,030
if you ever get tired,

234
00:13:11,030 --> 00:13:12,070
just take a break.

235
00:13:18,590 --> 00:13:19,270
Sweet.

236
00:13:20,110 --> 00:13:21,390
Wait on the rooftop after class.

237
00:13:21,710 --> 00:13:22,630
Let's talk.

238
00:13:28,310 --> 00:13:28,990
Who says you can

239
00:13:29,470 --> 00:13:30,510
command her?

240
00:13:35,750 --> 00:13:36,370
Next,

241
00:13:36,470 --> 00:13:37,310
go home

242
00:13:37,870 --> 00:13:39,510
and do more practices

243
00:13:39,830 --> 00:13:41,870
to strengthen your memory on the knowledge

244
00:13:42,190 --> 00:13:44,190
and improve your grades.

245
00:13:59,470 --> 00:14:00,270
Anran,

246
00:14:02,230 --> 00:14:04,070
you really know how to approach people.

247
00:14:04,990 --> 00:14:05,590
Tell me.

248
00:14:06,710 --> 00:14:08,710
What do you want from me?

249
00:14:10,390 --> 00:14:10,990
All right.

250
00:14:12,150 --> 00:14:13,750
Then I'll tell you the truth.

251
00:14:16,270 --> 00:14:18,670
I have always been an excellent student

252
00:14:18,670 --> 00:14:19,870
with strict parents.

253
00:14:19,870 --> 00:14:22,110
I only have dull guys around me like Ma Tian.

254
00:14:22,590 --> 00:14:23,830
So you don't like him, either.

255
00:14:24,670 --> 00:14:25,510
Huh?

256
00:14:28,550 --> 00:14:29,670
I just want to know

257
00:14:29,670 --> 00:14:30,950
how wind hounds like you

258
00:14:30,950 --> 00:14:31,670
live your lives.

259
00:14:41,510 --> 00:14:43,390
Am I really a wind hound?

260
00:14:44,070 --> 00:14:45,150
Of course!

261
00:14:45,270 --> 00:14:47,390
So now I'm after the wind, and you're after me.

262
00:14:49,230 --> 00:14:49,830
Okay.

263
00:14:51,310 --> 00:14:52,670
I'll be in charge from now on.

264
00:14:53,830 --> 00:14:56,630
Of course, you'll take notes and do my homework.

265
00:14:56,990 --> 00:14:58,270
Once I'm pleased,

266
00:14:58,270 --> 00:15:00,790
I'll take you to hang out with the other wind hounds.

267
00:15:00,790 --> 00:15:02,110
I'll even take you

268
00:15:02,230 --> 00:15:03,590
to my brother.

269
00:15:06,390 --> 00:15:07,590
Who is that?

270
00:15:07,590 --> 00:15:08,790
Could it be that Liu Wenqin

271
00:15:08,790 --> 00:15:10,310
you were bragging about?

272
00:15:10,990 --> 00:15:11,830
I wasn't bragging.

273
00:15:12,310 --> 00:15:13,430
Since you don't believe me,

274
00:15:13,430 --> 00:15:14,590
I swear I'll take you to him.

275
00:15:16,910 --> 00:15:19,150
I'll show you what a real

276
00:15:19,150 --> 00:15:20,790
wind hound is like.

277
00:15:28,190 --> 00:15:28,990
Chen Yuanyuan!

278
00:15:31,830 --> 00:15:33,030
What do you want now?

279
00:15:40,430 --> 00:15:42,230
It's your birthday today.

280
00:15:42,870 --> 00:15:44,190
I want to be the first

281
00:15:44,350 --> 00:15:46,830
to confess to you when you turn 17.

282
00:15:46,830 --> 00:15:47,550
He's so romantic.

283
00:15:52,830 --> 00:15:54,430
Since I was 13,

284
00:15:55,110 --> 00:15:56,590
you've always been the first

285
00:15:56,750 --> 00:15:58,110
to confess to me on my birthday.

286
00:15:59,790 --> 00:16:01,830
It's our destiny.

287
00:16:01,830 --> 00:16:02,670
Yuanyuan.

288
00:16:06,270 --> 00:16:07,750
Thank you for the cake.

289
00:16:08,230 --> 00:16:08,990
You're welcome.

290
00:16:09,750 --> 00:16:11,070
And, here.

291
00:16:11,550 --> 00:16:12,190
It's for you.

292
00:16:12,750 --> 00:16:13,790
What is it?

293
00:16:13,950 --> 00:16:15,150
A scarf.

294
00:16:15,150 --> 00:16:16,350
One for you.

295
00:16:16,830 --> 00:16:17,550
One for me.

296
00:16:18,870 --> 00:16:20,030
You can't buy it out there.

297
00:16:21,670 --> 00:16:22,750
It is very special.

298
00:16:22,750 --> 00:16:24,190
I split my long johns in two.

299
00:16:24,350 --> 00:16:25,030
Perfect cutting.

300
00:16:25,030 --> 00:16:26,350
He's ruining my work again.

301
00:16:27,190 --> 00:16:27,870
Wait a minute.

302
00:16:30,190 --> 00:16:31,870
What is it made of again?

303
00:16:31,950 --> 00:16:32,950
My long johns.

304
00:16:33,550 --> 00:16:34,630
In winter,

305
00:16:34,630 --> 00:16:36,030
we'll have couple scarves.

306
00:17:00,070 --> 00:17:00,710
Mouthy,

307
00:17:01,190 --> 00:17:02,550
what kind of guidance was that?

308
00:17:02,630 --> 00:17:03,550
It didn't work at all.

309
00:17:04,030 --> 00:17:04,630
Bro,

310
00:17:04,990 --> 00:17:06,630
with your IQ and your accent,

311
00:17:07,030 --> 00:17:08,390
it won't work even if I summon Shenron

312
00:17:08,390 --> 00:17:09,870
with seven Dragon Balls.

313
00:17:10,390 --> 00:17:11,470
What accent?

314
00:17:11,830 --> 00:17:12,430
I don't care.

315
00:17:12,710 --> 00:17:13,630
Write a new one.

316
00:17:13,750 --> 00:17:14,350
I'll buy it.

317
00:17:15,790 --> 00:17:17,870
You keep ruining my work with your practice.

318
00:17:18,230 --> 00:17:19,830
Do you think I'd sell you another one?

319
00:17:20,070 --> 00:17:21,190
I'll pay 80 yuan this time.

320
00:17:23,510 --> 00:17:24,150
Okay.

321
00:17:24,710 --> 00:17:27,070
But I'm only doing it for our brotherhood.

322
00:17:28,030 --> 00:17:28,870
That's my bro!

323
00:17:29,830 --> 00:17:31,750
What's the point of reading the pickup guidebook?

324
00:17:31,750 --> 00:17:33,310
Just learn from me.

325
00:17:33,310 --> 00:17:35,790
The new girl is after me so aggressively.

326
00:17:36,830 --> 00:17:37,750
How did you do it?

327
00:17:38,510 --> 00:17:39,430
With my charisma.

328
00:17:42,750 --> 00:17:44,030
Jiao, is there any noodles left?

329
00:17:44,110 --> 00:17:44,910
I'd like more.

330
00:17:44,910 --> 00:17:45,870
There's none.

331
00:17:45,870 --> 00:17:46,669
Noodles?

332
00:17:46,669 --> 00:17:47,550
I fed it to the dog.

333
00:17:50,470 --> 00:17:51,350
What dog?

334
00:17:51,350 --> 00:17:52,669
Why is it eating my noodles?

335
00:17:53,790 --> 00:17:55,270
When did she get a dog?

336
00:17:57,710 --> 00:17:59,189
I'll go feed the dog.

337
00:17:59,230 --> 00:18:00,270
You have a dog, too?

338
00:18:00,310 --> 00:18:01,189
We have dozens.

339
00:18:06,870 --> 00:18:07,750
I want a dog, too.

340
00:18:10,550 --> 00:18:11,910
What's wrong with you?

341
00:18:13,550 --> 00:18:14,950
Why are you pouting?

342
00:18:14,990 --> 00:18:15,950
Help me with the dishes.

343
00:18:19,070 --> 00:18:19,790
All right!

344
00:18:20,630 --> 00:18:22,230
I wondered which dog ate my noodles.

345
00:18:22,230 --> 00:18:23,310
So, it's you.

346
00:18:23,390 --> 00:18:24,030
Get lost.

347
00:18:24,430 --> 00:18:25,430
It's just one bowl of noodles.

348
00:18:26,470 --> 00:18:28,110
What do I eat if you eat it all?

349
00:18:28,350 --> 00:18:29,510
Feed on the air.

350
00:18:41,710 --> 00:18:42,390
My girl.

351
00:18:43,550 --> 00:18:44,310
Do you know

352
00:18:44,790 --> 00:18:46,710
that your uncle is my older brother?

353
00:18:47,230 --> 00:18:48,070
Of course.

354
00:18:49,790 --> 00:18:52,030
Back then, when he had girlfriends,

355
00:18:52,830 --> 00:18:53,830
I was upset, too.

356
00:18:54,670 --> 00:18:57,030
I always thought that he was only mine.

357
00:18:57,110 --> 00:18:59,070
I wouldn't let the other girls take him away.

358
00:19:00,150 --> 00:19:00,790
Actually,

359
00:19:01,230 --> 00:19:02,550
that's how you look right now.

360
00:19:03,110 --> 00:19:04,430
Mom, what are you talking about?

361
00:19:07,150 --> 00:19:08,990
You don't know what I'm talking about?

362
00:19:11,310 --> 00:19:12,430
Silly girl.

363
00:19:16,590 --> 00:19:17,710
That's fine.

364
00:19:36,230 --> 00:19:37,390
- Hello, Aunt. - Jiao.

365
00:19:37,390 --> 00:19:38,950
Uncle must have cheated on you.

366
00:19:38,990 --> 00:19:39,670
What?

367
00:19:39,670 --> 00:19:41,870
My mom said he had girlfriends.

368
00:19:41,870 --> 00:19:43,030
That bastard!

369
00:19:43,230 --> 00:19:44,350
I swear I'll kill him!

370
00:19:45,030 --> 00:19:45,750
Jiao.

371
00:19:46,750 --> 00:19:50,350
FlyinDance.

372
00:19:53,190 --> 00:19:54,710
Wilber Pan.

373
00:19:55,350 --> 00:19:56,310
This one looks good.

374
00:19:59,670 --> 00:20:01,750
COCO ACCEPTED YOUR FRIEND REQUEST.

375
00:20:04,830 --> 00:20:06,470
HIGH SCHOOL MOCK TEST

376
00:20:10,590 --> 00:20:11,670
Don't stay up too late.

377
00:20:11,950 --> 00:20:12,950
Okay. Don't worry.

378
00:20:25,750 --> 00:20:26,990
How are you?

379
00:20:27,790 --> 00:20:30,430
I am FlyinDance.

380
00:20:32,870 --> 00:20:34,030
What's up?

381
00:20:40,510 --> 00:20:41,430
In Wanzhou?

382
00:20:42,070 --> 00:20:44,630
(COCO: SO YOU'RE YOUNGER THAN ME, KIDDO.)
It's 10 p.m. I have to study.

383
00:20:44,670 --> 00:20:46,230
Catch you later.

384
00:20:50,830 --> 00:20:52,750
These questions are so easy.

385
00:21:01,470 --> 00:21:02,070
This example.

386
00:21:03,590 --> 00:21:04,390
I've repeated it

387
00:21:04,790 --> 00:21:05,390
so many times.

388
00:21:05,390 --> 00:21:06,310
What are you looking at?

389
00:21:07,230 --> 00:21:08,310
Check out the exercises

390
00:21:08,550 --> 00:21:10,270
on subject-verb agreement.

391
00:21:10,950 --> 00:21:13,150
Hey, there's nothing you can't do, huh?

392
00:21:16,430 --> 00:21:17,630
Write a break-up letter for me.

393
00:21:18,190 --> 00:21:18,870
To whom?

394
00:21:18,950 --> 00:21:20,030
None of your business.

395
00:21:20,030 --> 00:21:21,030
Then I can't.

396
00:21:21,790 --> 00:21:22,670
How about this?

397
00:21:23,990 --> 00:21:25,350
I'll give you a rough idea.

398
00:21:25,550 --> 00:21:26,590
Sum it up by yourself.

399
00:21:26,590 --> 00:21:28,310
And write it down as if you were me.

400
00:21:29,270 --> 00:21:29,870
Here we go.

401
00:21:31,590 --> 00:21:32,910
Someone

402
00:21:32,910 --> 00:21:34,750
grew up with me since we were kids.

403
00:21:34,750 --> 00:21:36,110
He would bully

404
00:21:36,270 --> 00:21:37,390
those who bullied me.

405
00:21:37,390 --> 00:21:38,390
Now, we've grown up,

406
00:21:39,350 --> 00:21:40,670
that bastard got a girl.

407
00:21:43,350 --> 00:21:44,110
Write it down.

408
00:21:52,230 --> 00:21:54,110
Since he's gone so far,

409
00:21:56,230 --> 00:21:57,150
I'll break up with him.

410
00:21:57,390 --> 00:21:58,790
Make it as resolute as possible.

411
00:22:01,190 --> 00:22:01,790
Done.

412
00:22:01,870 --> 00:22:02,750
So fast?

413
00:22:05,670 --> 00:22:06,430
Break-up letter.

414
00:22:07,510 --> 00:22:10,190
Honestly, I am reluctant to break up with you.

415
00:22:10,790 --> 00:22:12,030
Sweet talk me, and I will...

416
00:22:14,150 --> 00:22:15,270
I said so many things.

417
00:22:15,270 --> 00:22:16,630
You brushed me off in one sentence!

418
00:22:17,070 --> 00:22:18,270
I just wrote the truth.

419
00:22:38,470 --> 00:22:39,230
You did that wrong.

420
00:22:39,230 --> 00:22:40,230
Take notes for me.

421
00:23:04,430 --> 00:23:06,030
Why are you the only one here?

422
00:23:10,510 --> 00:23:11,390
You look exhausted

423
00:23:11,470 --> 00:23:12,910
before you start running.

424
00:23:15,030 --> 00:23:16,070
What's exhausting

425
00:23:16,150 --> 00:23:17,190
isn't the marathon.

426
00:23:17,910 --> 00:23:18,670
Let's go.

427
00:23:19,070 --> 00:23:20,310
Doggo.

428
00:23:20,310 --> 00:23:22,070
It's the fact that I have to deal with them.

429
00:23:22,190 --> 00:23:22,910
Guess what?

430
00:23:26,070 --> 00:23:27,150
They have been here

431
00:23:27,870 --> 00:23:28,990
since middle school.

432
00:23:30,310 --> 00:23:32,310
I saw the three of them grow up.

433
00:23:33,310 --> 00:23:34,550
It seems that

434
00:23:35,350 --> 00:23:36,590
they've always

435
00:23:36,590 --> 00:23:39,190
been doing and saying foolish and embarrassing things

436
00:23:39,630 --> 00:23:41,470
for no reason at all.

437
00:23:42,950 --> 00:23:43,550
And,

438
00:23:44,150 --> 00:23:45,590
they've always been together,

439
00:23:46,870 --> 00:23:47,950
looking even more stupid.

440
00:23:48,790 --> 00:23:49,630
You think so, too?

441
00:23:54,350 --> 00:23:55,230
In my opinion,

442
00:23:56,310 --> 00:23:58,350
that's what friends are for.

443
00:24:07,430 --> 00:24:09,510
When are we starting the formal training?

444
00:24:10,030 --> 00:24:12,230
When you become a team,

445
00:24:12,550 --> 00:24:14,790
we will start the formal training.

446
00:24:14,790 --> 00:24:16,310
Then we won't ever start.

447
00:24:29,750 --> 00:24:30,550
It doesn't help

448
00:24:30,830 --> 00:24:32,070
if you're going abroad.

449
00:24:32,070 --> 00:24:33,230
It's fine. I want to try.

450
00:25:07,750 --> 00:25:08,830
Are you stupid?

451
00:25:10,110 --> 00:25:11,830
Who'd believe it if you get a full mark?

452
00:25:15,710 --> 00:25:16,430
Right.

453
00:25:20,230 --> 00:25:21,430
Change something.

454
00:25:22,310 --> 00:25:23,790
It's okay. I have an idea.

455
00:25:24,790 --> 00:25:25,590
What?

456
00:25:27,230 --> 00:25:28,870
You can make a few mistakes.

457
00:25:39,710 --> 00:25:40,470
Jiao,

458
00:25:42,190 --> 00:25:43,310
do you want to copy mine?

459
00:25:44,750 --> 00:25:45,670
Save it!

460
00:25:47,150 --> 00:25:48,190
Full mark.

461
00:26:08,950 --> 00:26:10,030
Jiao, it's okay.

462
00:26:10,270 --> 00:26:10,890
Get lost!

463
00:26:11,150 --> 00:26:12,350
You scored eight?

464
00:26:12,350 --> 00:26:13,550
It's fine.

465
00:26:14,990 --> 00:26:16,070
You scored eight.

466
00:26:16,070 --> 00:26:16,990
Get lost!

467
00:26:17,550 --> 00:26:19,430
I worked on my own.

468
00:26:21,190 --> 00:26:22,990
You scored eight, Jiao.

469
00:26:22,990 --> 00:26:24,150
I didn't cheat.

470
00:26:24,150 --> 00:26:24,910
Me neither.

471
00:26:24,910 --> 00:26:26,230
I worked on my own.

472
00:26:26,350 --> 00:26:27,630
Teaty, how much did you score?

473
00:26:27,750 --> 00:26:28,430
Five.

474
00:26:28,630 --> 00:26:29,470
Five?

475
00:26:29,870 --> 00:26:30,910
I did okay on the test.

476
00:26:31,990 --> 00:26:33,950
It's truly astonishing.

477
00:26:34,310 --> 00:26:35,350
The first place this time

478
00:26:35,350 --> 00:26:36,350
is Tu Jun.

479
00:26:37,510 --> 00:26:39,190
And he actually scored higher

480
00:26:39,190 --> 00:26:41,190
than Anran, who was helping him.

481
00:26:41,790 --> 00:26:43,670
So, I suggest the helpers

482
00:26:43,670 --> 00:26:45,190
prioritize their own studies.

483
00:26:45,710 --> 00:26:47,830
Where there is a will, there is a way.

484
00:26:57,110 --> 00:26:57,910
Ma Tian,

485
00:26:58,430 --> 00:27:00,350
you came second in the exam.

486
00:27:00,870 --> 00:27:02,030
You don't seem very happy.

487
00:27:03,870 --> 00:27:05,110
You are quite shameless.

488
00:27:05,110 --> 00:27:06,230
Of course.

489
00:27:06,670 --> 00:27:09,550
I got the first place in the exam with my own efforts.

490
00:27:12,150 --> 00:27:12,750
Is that so?

491
00:27:22,390 --> 00:27:23,470
Anran,

492
00:27:23,630 --> 00:27:24,670
I don't know why

493
00:27:24,710 --> 00:27:26,550
but I'm in a very bad mood.

494
00:27:27,590 --> 00:27:29,350
He is questioning my ability.

495
00:27:32,790 --> 00:27:34,430
He really did it by himself.

496
00:27:44,590 --> 00:27:46,070
You got two pens and two notebooks.

497
00:27:46,430 --> 00:27:47,310
What else do you need?

498
00:27:54,590 --> 00:27:56,430
When is this going to end?

499
00:27:56,830 --> 00:27:57,630
Ignore him.

500
00:27:58,110 --> 00:27:59,190
What else can I do?

501
00:27:59,710 --> 00:28:01,030
I even got transferred.

502
00:28:01,030 --> 00:28:02,350
I can't just give up.

503
00:28:03,710 --> 00:28:05,550
This Doggo is outrageous.

504
00:28:06,710 --> 00:28:07,550
Yeah.

505
00:28:07,830 --> 00:28:09,470
I can't even do better than him in tests.

506
00:28:13,070 --> 00:28:13,830
I got your things.

507
00:28:14,150 --> 00:28:14,770
Let's go.

508
00:28:16,510 --> 00:28:17,430
It's your senior year.

509
00:28:17,430 --> 00:28:19,990
And you never ask any questions,

510
00:28:20,590 --> 00:28:22,590
like you're all going to top universities.

511
00:28:23,790 --> 00:28:24,870
Okay. Listen up.

512
00:28:24,870 --> 00:28:26,470
Characteristics of urban garbage...

513
00:28:29,870 --> 00:28:30,830
I noticed that

514
00:28:30,830 --> 00:28:32,430
your notebook was a mess,

515
00:28:32,430 --> 00:28:33,470
and your pen wouldn't write.

516
00:28:33,550 --> 00:28:34,710
So, I got you some.

517
00:28:41,550 --> 00:28:43,270
I'll take you out next class.

518
00:28:44,110 --> 00:28:44,990
Can we go out?

519
00:28:44,990 --> 00:28:46,390
Of course. I got this.

520
00:28:46,390 --> 00:28:47,750
You're right, Doggo.

521
00:28:47,910 --> 00:28:49,350
Meet me at the school gate.

522
00:28:49,350 --> 00:28:49,990
Okay.

523
00:29:12,590 --> 00:29:14,830
Doggo, I thought we were meeting downstairs.

524
00:29:14,910 --> 00:29:16,790
Class was beginning and you still didn't come.

525
00:29:21,710 --> 00:29:22,630
What's wrong?

526
00:29:28,230 --> 00:29:29,910
DOGGO IS AN A-HOLE

527
00:29:33,630 --> 00:29:34,470
It wasn't me.

528
00:29:36,190 --> 00:29:37,430
It's the one you gave me.

529
00:29:37,430 --> 00:29:38,270
I swear it wasn't me.

530
00:29:38,270 --> 00:29:38,990
That's enough.

531
00:29:49,630 --> 00:29:50,270
What's wrong?

532
00:29:50,270 --> 00:29:51,110
Stop pretending.

533
00:29:52,590 --> 00:29:53,910
I just can't stand it.

534
00:29:54,070 --> 00:29:55,830
Are you becoming as childish as him?

535
00:30:12,190 --> 00:30:13,350
Jiao.

536
00:30:15,870 --> 00:30:16,510
What's wrong?

537
00:30:17,550 --> 00:30:19,190
People nowadays are so mean.

538
00:30:21,990 --> 00:30:22,630
Is that so?

539
00:30:23,270 --> 00:30:23,870
Yeah.

540
00:30:24,310 --> 00:30:25,030
Yeah.

541
00:30:25,150 --> 00:30:26,990
They humiliate me with their gift.

542
00:30:28,630 --> 00:30:29,790
I told you it wasn't me.

543
00:30:29,790 --> 00:30:31,190
What's the point of arguing?

544
00:30:31,190 --> 00:30:32,750
You two are on the same side.

545
00:30:33,270 --> 00:30:36,470
I'm so wronged.

546
00:30:38,150 --> 00:30:39,110
I'm so sad.

547
00:30:41,110 --> 00:30:42,590
What do you want?

548
00:30:42,670 --> 00:30:44,430
It's indeed none of her business.

549
00:30:44,670 --> 00:30:46,030
I'm sorry, okay?

550
00:30:48,630 --> 00:30:50,670
Jiao, he's shouting at me.

551
00:30:55,590 --> 00:30:56,630
Do you feel wronged?

552
00:30:56,630 --> 00:30:57,430
You two are so mean.

553
00:30:57,430 --> 00:30:58,270
Yeah.

554
00:30:59,110 --> 00:30:59,870
What now?

555
00:31:00,030 --> 00:31:00,990
I feel awful.

556
00:31:01,150 --> 00:31:02,030
What can I do?

557
00:31:02,030 --> 00:31:03,590
I did offend him first.

558
00:31:04,230 --> 00:31:05,270
Is this what you want to do?

559
00:31:06,910 --> 00:31:07,590
What?

560
00:31:28,870 --> 00:31:29,790
Jiao,

561
00:31:29,790 --> 00:31:30,910
why did you hit me?

562
00:31:30,910 --> 00:31:32,110
Stop acting.

563
00:31:33,790 --> 00:31:34,390
Okay.

564
00:31:34,470 --> 00:31:35,090
Got it.

565
00:32:05,190 --> 00:32:05,790
What?

566
00:32:06,350 --> 00:32:07,550
Are you still mad?

567
00:32:07,550 --> 00:32:09,510
I'll help you with another set of mock tests.

568
00:32:12,910 --> 00:32:14,350
Teaty, what are you doing?

569
00:32:14,670 --> 00:32:15,590
Playing Five in a Row.

570
00:32:15,590 --> 00:32:16,470
Playing chess.

571
00:32:17,470 --> 00:32:17,790
Let me.

572
00:32:17,790 --> 00:32:18,630
I'm done.

573
00:32:18,710 --> 00:32:19,430
Go ahead.

574
00:32:19,430 --> 00:32:20,630
I've got five in a row.

575
00:32:22,030 --> 00:32:22,630
Stop it.

576
00:32:22,630 --> 00:32:24,030
Do you have to cheat every time?

577
00:32:24,830 --> 00:32:25,510
Let's go.

578
00:32:44,390 --> 00:32:45,010
What?

579
00:32:47,270 --> 00:32:47,890
Let's go.

580
00:32:49,270 --> 00:32:49,870
Where to?

581
00:32:50,510 --> 00:32:51,190
You know.

582
00:32:54,390 --> 00:32:56,070
There. I'll climb up first.

583
00:32:56,190 --> 00:32:58,550
Step on the ping-pong table to climb up.

584
00:32:58,710 --> 00:32:59,790
I'll pull you up.

585
00:33:00,070 --> 00:33:01,390
Over the wall?

586
00:33:02,070 --> 00:33:02,870
Scared, huh?

587
00:33:05,750 --> 00:33:07,110
Tell you what.

588
00:33:07,470 --> 00:33:08,670
Only me, Doggo,

589
00:33:09,070 --> 00:33:10,230
can climb this wall

590
00:33:10,230 --> 00:33:11,310
in our school.

591
00:33:11,630 --> 00:33:12,830
Teaty, Mouthy and the others

592
00:33:13,670 --> 00:33:14,790
can't climb it at all.

593
00:33:19,110 --> 00:33:21,070
We're climbing the wall in our senior year!

594
00:33:22,310 --> 00:33:23,510
Hurry up!

595
00:33:23,710 --> 00:33:24,950
We may get caught by the security.

596
00:33:25,950 --> 00:33:26,550
Hurry up!

597
00:33:28,430 --> 00:33:29,030
Okay.

598
00:33:36,190 --> 00:33:37,030
Where are they?

599
00:33:40,710 --> 00:33:42,670
Don't you know your best friend is skipping class?

600
00:33:43,910 --> 00:33:45,590
So, where is your best friend?

601
00:33:49,790 --> 00:33:50,830
Don't worry.

602
00:33:50,830 --> 00:33:51,950
Anran won't cause trouble.

603
00:33:53,310 --> 00:33:54,390
Maybe they have things to do.

604
00:33:54,470 --> 00:33:56,630
Why can't they do it in the classroom?

605
00:34:02,670 --> 00:34:03,270
Poker face.

606
00:34:03,270 --> 00:34:04,110
Expressionless.

607
00:34:04,110 --> 00:34:05,230
It just pisses me off!

608
00:34:09,830 --> 00:34:10,630
What?

609
00:34:10,630 --> 00:34:11,350
Are you angry?

610
00:34:39,430 --> 00:34:40,670
Doggo, have some.

611
00:34:40,670 --> 00:34:41,510
Doggo.

612
00:34:42,630 --> 00:34:43,390
Want some?

613
00:34:44,150 --> 00:34:46,630
No. Never mind. No.

614
00:34:48,750 --> 00:34:49,830
Take it.

615
00:34:51,110 --> 00:34:51,749
Doggo.

616
00:34:53,070 --> 00:34:54,150
What a beautiful girl.

617
00:34:54,749 --> 00:34:55,350
Impressive!

618
00:34:55,470 --> 00:34:56,590
A life to enjoy.

619
00:34:56,709 --> 00:34:57,350
Have a drink.

620
00:34:57,670 --> 00:34:58,789
No, no.

621
00:34:58,789 --> 00:34:59,910
We're minors.

622
00:34:59,910 --> 00:35:01,350
Minors can't drink.

623
00:35:01,350 --> 00:35:02,390
All right.

624
00:35:02,390 --> 00:35:03,309
You guys have fun.

625
00:35:06,190 --> 00:35:07,430
Chicken steaks?

626
00:35:07,590 --> 00:35:08,670
No? Forget it.

627
00:35:09,590 --> 00:35:10,269
First time here?

628
00:35:14,110 --> 00:35:14,789
Hold it.

629
00:35:14,789 --> 00:35:16,070
What if you get lost?

630
00:35:20,430 --> 00:35:21,670
Look at you girls!

631
00:35:28,309 --> 00:35:29,870
I can't drink. Seriously.

632
00:35:29,870 --> 00:35:30,830
I can't drink.

633
00:35:31,070 --> 00:35:32,950
Minors can't drink.

634
00:35:33,990 --> 00:35:35,430
By the way, is Qin here?

635
00:35:35,430 --> 00:35:36,870
No.

636
00:35:36,870 --> 00:35:38,150
Go ahead. Enjoy yourselves.

637
00:35:39,390 --> 00:35:40,270
No, no.

638
00:35:41,030 --> 00:35:42,150
What are you doing?

639
00:35:46,510 --> 00:35:47,590
Hey, you guys!

640
00:35:49,510 --> 00:35:50,470
Enjoy.

641
00:35:52,190 --> 00:35:52,990
Where's your brother?

642
00:35:54,270 --> 00:35:55,750
He's not here today.

643
00:35:55,750 --> 00:35:56,670
Rain check.

644
00:36:01,470 --> 00:36:03,230
Their grill is amazing. Want some?

645
00:36:14,470 --> 00:36:15,350
What's wrong?

646
00:36:15,750 --> 00:36:16,710
Nothing.

647
00:36:18,550 --> 00:36:19,870
I told you.

648
00:36:19,870 --> 00:36:21,110
You can't adapt to the environment

649
00:36:21,110 --> 00:36:22,390
and the people.

650
00:36:22,830 --> 00:36:23,630
What did I do?

651
00:36:28,630 --> 00:36:29,350
Look at you,

652
00:36:29,910 --> 00:36:31,230
always in the school uniform.

653
00:36:31,790 --> 00:36:32,910
What's wrong with that?

654
00:36:32,910 --> 00:36:34,590
You saw what those girls were wearing.

655
00:36:34,670 --> 00:36:36,550
I'm a man of pride, too.

656
00:36:40,990 --> 00:36:41,910
I can do that.

657
00:36:49,710 --> 00:36:50,910
A-Anran,

658
00:36:51,230 --> 00:36:52,550
w-what are you doing?

659
00:38:33,590 --> 00:38:34,790
Do your own homework today.

660
00:38:45,190 --> 00:38:46,230
That's me here.

661
00:38:46,910 --> 00:38:47,750
- Okay. - Bye.

662
00:38:47,950 --> 00:38:48,670
Bye bye.

663
00:39:51,750 --> 00:39:54,510
Guys, do you think it's fine

664
00:39:54,790 --> 00:39:56,710
to be poor at our age?

665
00:39:57,830 --> 00:39:59,470
What can we do?

666
00:39:59,470 --> 00:40:00,590
We're still at school.

667
00:40:02,070 --> 00:40:02,750
Doggo,

668
00:40:03,150 --> 00:40:04,870
why did you say that out of nowhere?

669
00:40:04,910 --> 00:40:05,510
Yeah.

670
00:40:05,750 --> 00:40:06,430
Why?

671
00:40:07,190 --> 00:40:08,470
I walked Anran home today.

672
00:40:09,830 --> 00:40:11,510
I knew it!

673
00:40:12,070 --> 00:40:13,630
Seeing her in a big villa

674
00:40:14,270 --> 00:40:15,150
and playing the piano,

675
00:40:16,110 --> 00:40:17,310
I found it high-class.

676
00:40:18,630 --> 00:40:20,990
You met a rich girl and forgot who you were.

677
00:40:21,510 --> 00:40:23,030
What does her villa and piano

678
00:40:23,030 --> 00:40:23,990
have anything to do with you?

679
00:40:23,990 --> 00:40:25,110
I was just thinking about it.

680
00:40:26,870 --> 00:40:29,070
If we keep fooling around and remain poor

681
00:40:29,550 --> 00:40:30,150
without

682
00:40:30,870 --> 00:40:32,190
any ambitions,

683
00:40:32,470 --> 00:40:33,830
will we be unlovable?

684
00:40:35,190 --> 00:40:37,190
You're just afraid that Anran will find you poor.

685
00:40:37,190 --> 00:40:38,430
You butcher.

686
00:40:41,590 --> 00:40:42,830
I can't talk to you.

687
00:40:42,830 --> 00:40:43,550
What a waste.

688
00:40:57,670 --> 00:40:59,950
Take the bomb, pretty face.

689
00:40:59,950 --> 00:41:01,030
Who's "pretty face"?

690
00:41:01,950 --> 00:41:03,430
The one seeking revenge.

691
00:41:06,870 --> 00:41:07,590
Team lead.

692
00:41:09,790 --> 00:41:11,030
What are we training on next?

693
00:41:11,710 --> 00:41:12,430
Anything.

694
00:41:12,950 --> 00:41:14,630
Just go back when it's over.

695
00:41:16,910 --> 00:41:17,750
How about going

696
00:41:17,870 --> 00:41:19,270
for a run outside today?

697
00:41:19,630 --> 00:41:21,110
At this hour,

698
00:41:21,110 --> 00:41:23,030
it's so much fun to go out.

699
00:41:23,190 --> 00:41:25,070
It'd be so much livelier than at school.

700
00:41:25,830 --> 00:41:26,470
Are we going?

701
00:41:27,190 --> 00:41:30,310
You might want to ask our vengeful team lead Ma.

702
00:41:32,310 --> 00:41:33,030
Sure.

703
00:41:33,870 --> 00:41:35,430
We'll just go for a run.

704
00:41:36,470 --> 00:41:37,070
Okay.

705
00:41:41,310 --> 00:41:42,070
How do you feel?

706
00:41:43,310 --> 00:41:43,950
Is it better

707
00:41:43,950 --> 00:41:45,150
to run out here?

708
00:41:46,550 --> 00:41:47,710
Is it more exciting?

709
00:41:53,230 --> 00:41:54,350
They're here! Run!

710
00:41:54,350 --> 00:41:55,470
Run! Hurry up!

711
00:41:55,470 --> 00:41:56,070
Don't run.

712
00:42:00,230 --> 00:42:00,850
Oh no!

713
00:42:03,790 --> 00:42:04,390
Mom.

714
00:42:05,310 --> 00:42:05,910
Mom.

715
00:42:06,270 --> 00:42:06,870
Run!

716
00:42:11,670 --> 00:42:12,750
What's wrong?

717
00:42:12,830 --> 00:42:13,670
Doggo,

718
00:42:13,670 --> 00:42:14,990
is that his mom?

719
00:42:18,870 --> 00:42:21,510
Stop! Don't run!

720
00:42:23,870 --> 00:42:25,070
I said stop.

721
00:42:36,510 --> 00:42:37,390
Go!

722
00:42:37,870 --> 00:42:39,470
Go!

723
00:42:47,830 --> 00:42:49,510
Stop! Don't run!

724
00:43:07,470 --> 00:43:08,390
Stop!

725
00:43:08,390 --> 00:43:09,150
Are you mad dogs?

726
00:43:09,190 --> 00:43:09,990
Why are you so fast?

727
00:43:10,630 --> 00:43:12,030
Yeah, we are mad dogs!

728
00:43:22,030 --> 00:43:22,670
Mom.

729
00:43:23,350 --> 00:43:24,310
Go home first.

730
00:43:24,590 --> 00:43:25,950
Let me talk to them a bit.

731
00:43:25,990 --> 00:43:27,150
Alright. Go ahead.

732
00:43:27,550 --> 00:43:28,430
Thank you.

733
00:43:29,430 --> 00:43:30,150
It's fine.

734
00:43:33,550 --> 00:43:35,190
I told you so, team lead.

735
00:43:35,190 --> 00:43:36,150
You didn't believe me.

736
00:43:36,430 --> 00:43:37,630
I run pretty well.

737
00:43:38,950 --> 00:43:39,870
I have to push

738
00:43:39,870 --> 00:43:41,670
the cart up the hill sometimes.

739
00:43:43,150 --> 00:43:43,790
Well.

740
00:43:44,030 --> 00:43:45,310
Anyway,

741
00:43:45,510 --> 00:43:46,750
any extra point counts.

742
00:43:47,110 --> 00:43:48,870
If he takes the exam again,

743
00:43:49,210 --> 00:43:49,830
he...

744
00:43:49,830 --> 00:43:50,710
he'll be truly old.

745
00:43:53,790 --> 00:43:54,790
Let's train early tomorrow.

746
00:43:56,470 --> 00:43:57,070
Okay.

747
00:43:57,510 --> 00:43:59,270
We'll do a serious training tomorrow.

748
00:43:59,470 --> 00:44:00,230
Okay.

749
00:44:01,470 --> 00:44:02,190
Let's go.

750
00:44:43,550 --> 00:44:44,590
Hello, coach.

751
00:44:48,110 --> 00:44:49,190
Hello, sir.

752
00:44:51,230 --> 00:44:52,550
What a team.

753
00:44:54,070 --> 00:44:55,190
You went running together?

754
00:44:55,510 --> 00:44:56,270
Yeah.

755
00:44:56,790 --> 00:44:57,750
Have some drinks.

756
00:44:59,390 --> 00:45:00,550
Thank you.

757
00:45:03,790 --> 00:45:04,590
Thank you.

758
00:45:06,750 --> 00:45:07,950
I didn't run.

759
00:45:12,190 --> 00:45:14,150
It's good to see you so ambitious.

760
00:45:14,150 --> 00:45:15,070
Will you come over

761
00:45:15,070 --> 00:45:16,350
this weekend for my birthday?

762
00:45:16,710 --> 00:45:17,350
All right.

763
00:45:17,350 --> 00:45:18,150
I won't go.

764
00:45:24,350 --> 00:45:25,190
Jiao,

765
00:45:25,910 --> 00:45:26,670
if you don't go,

766
00:45:26,990 --> 00:45:28,110
we won't, either.

767
00:45:32,430 --> 00:45:33,430
Alright.

768
00:45:33,510 --> 00:45:34,470
I'll do you a favor.

769
00:45:37,750 --> 00:45:38,830
Thank you, Jiao.

770
00:45:45,470 --> 00:45:46,150
Your noodles.

771
00:45:48,190 --> 00:45:48,950
Jiao,

772
00:45:49,030 --> 00:45:50,190
what should I get

773
00:45:50,350 --> 00:45:51,470
her for her birthday?

774
00:45:56,350 --> 00:45:57,350
I'm 17 years old.

775
00:45:57,710 --> 00:45:58,430
I know.

776
00:45:58,430 --> 00:45:59,630
In the past 17 years,

777
00:45:59,930 --> 00:46:00,550
have you ever

778
00:46:00,550 --> 00:46:01,670
bought me a birthday gift?

779
00:46:03,630 --> 00:46:04,470
We're buddies.

780
00:46:04,990 --> 00:46:06,150
Gifts are for outsiders.

781
00:46:09,710 --> 00:46:11,390
Pork liver, of course.

782
00:46:11,390 --> 00:46:12,270
For real?

783
00:46:12,270 --> 00:46:13,430
Just think about her face.

784
00:46:13,510 --> 00:46:14,670
She's as white as a sheet.

785
00:46:14,990 --> 00:46:16,510
She's obviously anemic.

786
00:46:17,230 --> 00:46:18,590
Of course, she needs pork liver

787
00:46:18,670 --> 00:46:19,910
for more iron.

788
00:46:27,230 --> 00:46:28,590
Jiao, what about my noodles?

789
00:46:28,870 --> 00:46:30,230
I'm feeding it to the dog.

790
00:46:38,470 --> 00:46:39,390
Pork liver.

791
00:46:41,070 --> 00:46:41,950
For iron.

792
00:46:43,630 --> 00:46:45,190
The houses here are so big.

793
00:46:46,110 --> 00:46:46,710
Look.

794
00:46:47,190 --> 00:46:48,470
That one looks like a castle.

795
00:46:48,470 --> 00:46:49,870
Don't act like a peasant.

796
00:46:49,990 --> 00:46:51,230
Stop overreacting.

797
00:46:52,830 --> 00:46:53,990
Is that her house?

798
00:46:53,990 --> 00:46:54,870
I think so.

799
00:46:55,910 --> 00:46:56,910
Is that a garden?

800
00:46:57,510 --> 00:46:58,550
What a big garden!

801
00:47:07,270 --> 00:47:08,910
Anran, we are here.

802
00:47:08,910 --> 00:47:09,590
Anran.

803
00:47:09,830 --> 00:47:10,510
Shush.

804
00:47:11,270 --> 00:47:12,230
They have a doorbell.

805
00:47:13,630 --> 00:47:14,470
So classy.

806
00:47:14,470 --> 00:47:15,430
Fancy doorbell.

807
00:47:16,150 --> 00:47:16,830
Where do I press?

808
00:47:17,670 --> 00:47:18,390
I think it can...

809
00:47:20,750 --> 00:47:21,470
You're here.

810
00:47:23,030 --> 00:47:23,630
Come in.

811
00:47:26,350 --> 00:47:27,310
We're coming in.

812
00:47:27,390 --> 00:47:28,070
Come on in.

813
00:47:28,270 --> 00:47:29,350
What a big chandelier!

814
00:47:29,630 --> 00:47:30,350
Happy birthday.

815
00:47:31,070 --> 00:47:32,470
Have some fruits.

816
00:47:33,790 --> 00:47:34,510
Thank you, auntie.

817
00:47:40,870 --> 00:47:41,630
Have some.

818
00:47:42,070 --> 00:47:42,790
Have some.

819
00:47:43,790 --> 00:47:44,790
Have a tomato.

820
00:47:45,590 --> 00:47:46,270
It's a tomato?

821
00:47:46,270 --> 00:47:47,190
This is an apple.

822
00:47:47,190 --> 00:47:48,270
Tomato. Totally.

823
00:47:48,270 --> 00:47:48,910
Apple.

824
00:47:49,150 --> 00:47:50,430
They look the same.

825
00:47:50,430 --> 00:47:51,070
She's kidding.

826
00:47:52,830 --> 00:47:53,710
Go ahead.

827
00:47:54,150 --> 00:47:54,790
I'll go.

828
00:47:54,790 --> 00:47:55,990
I'll go.

829
00:47:58,910 --> 00:47:59,510
Ma Tian is here.

830
00:48:00,710 --> 00:48:01,750
You invited him, too?

831
00:48:01,870 --> 00:48:02,470
Yeah.

832
00:48:03,430 --> 00:48:04,950
Ran, Ma Tian is here.

833
00:48:06,550 --> 00:48:07,590
Happy birthday.

834
00:48:07,670 --> 00:48:08,289
Thank you.

835
00:48:09,590 --> 00:48:10,190
Wait.

836
00:48:12,390 --> 00:48:13,270
How is it

837
00:48:13,270 --> 00:48:14,670
a birthday without a gift?

838
00:48:14,790 --> 00:48:15,430
Thank you.

839
00:48:18,350 --> 00:48:19,110
Ran,

840
00:48:19,470 --> 00:48:20,390
I guess all of them

841
00:48:20,390 --> 00:48:21,670
got you presents.

842
00:48:29,630 --> 00:48:30,510
I got you something.

843
00:48:30,990 --> 00:48:32,030
Forget it.

844
00:48:32,470 --> 00:48:33,390
He didn't.

845
00:48:33,390 --> 00:48:34,190
I did for real.

846
00:48:34,870 --> 00:48:36,270
Forget it. Don't do it.

847
00:48:36,470 --> 00:48:37,310
I was kidding, Doggo.

848
00:48:37,430 --> 00:48:38,470
Why are you so stingy?

849
00:48:38,470 --> 00:48:39,550
They invited us to dinner.

850
00:48:40,910 --> 00:48:41,710
Happy birthday.

851
00:48:46,870 --> 00:48:47,710
Thank you.

852
00:48:48,110 --> 00:48:48,750
Take a look.

853
00:48:48,750 --> 00:48:49,470
See if you like it.

854
00:49:00,670 --> 00:49:01,430
I can tell

855
00:49:01,510 --> 00:49:02,350
by your complexion

856
00:49:02,430 --> 00:49:03,270
that you are anemic.

857
00:49:03,270 --> 00:49:04,150
Fresh pork liver

858
00:49:04,150 --> 00:49:04,769
for extra iron.

859
00:49:06,150 --> 00:49:07,430
What a special friend.

860
00:49:08,350 --> 00:49:09,270
Very considerate.

861
00:49:10,270 --> 00:49:10,910
Auntie,

862
00:49:10,910 --> 00:49:12,070
you're welcome.

863
00:49:12,590 --> 00:49:13,270
Cook it now

864
00:49:13,350 --> 00:49:14,670
and we'll have it in a minute.

865
00:49:15,310 --> 00:49:15,930
Yeah.

866
00:49:17,790 --> 00:49:18,550
We have enough dishes.

867
00:49:18,750 --> 00:49:19,870
Yeah. It's enough.

868
00:49:19,870 --> 00:49:20,790
It's enough. For real.

869
00:49:20,790 --> 00:49:21,790
All right. Sit down.

870
00:49:21,790 --> 00:49:22,670
How's it enough?

871
00:49:23,230 --> 00:49:24,470
Auntie, a birthday dinner

872
00:49:24,470 --> 00:49:25,950
can never have enough dishes.

873
00:49:26,070 --> 00:49:27,830
Fresh pork liver for stir-fry.

874
00:49:28,150 --> 00:49:28,870
Auntie,

875
00:49:28,870 --> 00:49:30,750
are you saving it as a gift for us?

876
00:49:31,310 --> 00:49:31,910
Yeah.

877
00:49:33,870 --> 00:49:34,490
Okay.

878
00:49:36,790 --> 00:49:37,910
Thank you, auntie.

879
00:49:39,590 --> 00:49:40,550
We have a meal.

880
00:49:41,270 --> 00:49:42,190
We gave presents.

881
00:49:45,950 --> 00:49:47,030
Great pork liver.

882
00:49:47,030 --> 00:49:48,150
The liver is so delicious!

883
00:49:48,150 --> 00:49:49,270
Show some manners.

884
00:49:49,790 --> 00:49:50,390
Here.

885
00:49:50,390 --> 00:49:51,470
Who's drinking with me?

886
00:49:52,710 --> 00:49:53,750
- Here. - Cheers.

887
00:49:54,150 --> 00:49:55,150
Happy birthday.

888
00:49:55,150 --> 00:49:56,350
Thank you.

889
00:50:00,630 --> 00:50:01,470
Right, Ma Tian,

890
00:50:01,750 --> 00:50:02,590
I have a question.

891
00:50:03,430 --> 00:50:05,190
You said there was a bad boy at school

892
00:50:06,630 --> 00:50:08,150
trying to approach

893
00:50:08,390 --> 00:50:09,670
Anran at every chance.

894
00:50:09,969 --> 00:50:11,390
- Who? - Who is it?

895
00:50:11,390 --> 00:50:12,310
- Who is that? - Nobody.

896
00:50:12,310 --> 00:50:12,910
Tell me.

897
00:50:12,990 --> 00:50:13,790
Nobody at all.

898
00:50:14,190 --> 00:50:15,110
Kids at this age

899
00:50:15,870 --> 00:50:17,470
can't be bad.

900
00:50:17,710 --> 00:50:18,830
They're just naughty.

901
00:50:18,990 --> 00:50:19,910
Not necessarily.

902
00:50:20,030 --> 00:50:20,870
Not necessarily.

903
00:50:21,110 --> 00:50:22,230
No, listen to me.

904
00:50:22,230 --> 00:50:24,990
Being naughty is different from being bad.

905
00:50:25,990 --> 00:50:28,110
Naughty is somehow

906
00:50:28,110 --> 00:50:29,790
kind of cute.

907
00:50:29,790 --> 00:50:31,150
They're all naughty, right?

908
00:50:31,310 --> 00:50:32,350
Yeah, uncle.

909
00:50:33,110 --> 00:50:34,590
But what about the bad boy?

910
00:50:34,590 --> 00:50:35,710
Maybe

911
00:50:35,710 --> 00:50:38,230
he's from a poor family, right?

912
00:50:38,230 --> 00:50:39,910
He lives a tough life.

913
00:50:39,910 --> 00:50:40,910
Being poor is fine.

914
00:50:40,910 --> 00:50:42,710
The problem is that his parents

915
00:50:42,710 --> 00:50:44,710
may have failed to educate him.

916
00:50:46,430 --> 00:50:47,430
Uncle, you're drunk.

917
00:50:47,590 --> 00:50:48,630
How can he be drunk?

918
00:50:48,630 --> 00:50:49,550
Uncle is right.

919
00:50:49,550 --> 00:50:50,510
He's drinking Baijiu.

920
00:50:50,790 --> 00:50:52,030
That's right. I'm not drunk.

921
00:50:52,030 --> 00:50:53,150
Dad, would you like some soup?

922
00:50:53,150 --> 00:50:54,630
No, no. Listen to me.

923
00:50:54,630 --> 00:50:56,510
I've asked your teacher.

924
00:50:57,470 --> 00:50:59,190
That kid is called...

925
00:50:59,190 --> 00:50:59,710
What?

926
00:50:59,710 --> 00:51:00,830
Something Jun.

927
00:51:01,150 --> 00:51:02,070
Li Jun!

928
00:51:02,070 --> 00:51:02,950
From Class 3!

929
00:51:03,550 --> 00:51:04,630
We'll beat him at school!

930
00:51:06,950 --> 00:51:08,150
I remember!

931
00:51:08,350 --> 00:51:08,950
That's him!

932
00:51:10,230 --> 00:51:11,350
His family

933
00:51:11,350 --> 00:51:12,110
butchers pigs.

934
00:51:12,110 --> 00:51:12,830
Butchers...

935
00:51:24,710 --> 00:51:25,350
Tell you what.

936
00:51:26,030 --> 00:51:27,350
Butchers like them...

937
00:51:29,230 --> 00:51:30,510
Excuse me, uncle.

938
00:51:30,510 --> 00:51:33,150
Is a kid's character totally determined by the family?

939
00:51:34,830 --> 00:51:35,790
Not necessarily.

940
00:51:35,950 --> 00:51:37,110
But tell you what.

941
00:51:37,110 --> 00:51:38,990
The growth of a child

942
00:51:38,990 --> 00:51:41,110
starts with his family.

943
00:51:41,110 --> 00:51:42,150
If his family

944
00:51:42,150 --> 00:51:43,710
fails to educate him,

945
00:51:43,710 --> 00:51:45,510
then even when he gets to school,

946
00:51:45,750 --> 00:51:47,350
the teachers can't do much.

947
00:51:48,670 --> 00:51:49,830
For example...

948
00:51:49,830 --> 00:51:51,030
I can't convince you anyhow.

949
00:51:52,990 --> 00:51:54,910
Well, don't eat the pork liver from a bad kid.

950
00:51:57,009 --> 00:51:57,630
Uncle, auntie,

951
00:51:57,630 --> 00:51:58,470
I have to go.

952
00:52:00,070 --> 00:52:01,150
We're leaving, too.

953
00:52:01,830 --> 00:52:03,150
We haven't eaten the cake yet.

954
00:52:03,190 --> 00:52:04,190
We don't deserve it.

955
00:52:13,110 --> 00:52:14,190
You always think you're right.

956
00:52:14,190 --> 00:52:15,350
But in fact, you are

957
00:52:15,350 --> 00:52:16,230
strongly biased.

958
00:52:17,950 --> 00:52:18,830
Any other exits?

959
00:52:18,870 --> 00:52:19,470
Where is he?

960
00:52:22,070 --> 00:52:22,870
It's all your fault!

961
00:52:23,430 --> 00:52:24,390
What do you want?

962
00:52:24,390 --> 00:52:25,710
That was earlier before.

963
00:52:25,710 --> 00:52:27,070
Prestigious guys like you

964
00:52:27,070 --> 00:52:28,230
think highly of yourselves

965
00:52:28,230 --> 00:52:29,550
and have no respect for others.

966
00:52:47,190 --> 00:52:47,809
What?

967
00:52:50,990 --> 00:52:52,430
I'm really sorry about that.

968
00:52:53,390 --> 00:52:54,950
Please don't be mad, Doggo.

969
00:53:02,390 --> 00:53:03,750
It's your birthday.

970
00:53:04,310 --> 00:53:04,929
It's fine.

971
00:53:06,590 --> 00:53:07,350
You're fine now?

972
00:53:11,270 --> 00:53:12,990
A great man knows when to yield.

973
00:53:17,430 --> 00:53:19,190
Did you have the cake?

974
00:53:19,790 --> 00:53:20,950
I came out looking for you.

975
00:53:24,790 --> 00:53:25,870
Let me take you somewhere.

976
00:53:26,590 --> 00:53:27,249
Where?

977
00:53:35,030 --> 00:53:36,390
Wait here for me.

978
00:53:36,710 --> 00:53:37,790
Where are you going?

979
00:54:19,750 --> 00:54:21,590
Hello, Doggo.

980
00:54:21,950 --> 00:54:22,790
What is this?

981
00:54:38,390 --> 00:54:39,510
You want to put 17 candles

982
00:54:39,710 --> 00:54:41,270
on such a small cake?

983
00:54:44,230 --> 00:54:44,830
Come on.

984
00:54:44,870 --> 00:54:45,950
One candle will do.

985
00:54:54,550 --> 00:54:57,470
Happy birthday to you.

986
00:54:57,470 --> 00:55:01,390
Happy birthday to you.

987
00:55:01,390 --> 00:55:04,910
Happy birthday to you.

988
00:55:04,910 --> 00:55:08,910
Happy birthday to you.

989
00:55:09,550 --> 00:55:10,150
Make a wish.

990
00:55:20,430 --> 00:55:22,550
Past and present

991
00:55:23,070 --> 00:55:26,270
Gone and never return

992
00:55:29,910 --> 00:55:32,030
Red fallen leaves

993
00:55:32,030 --> 00:55:36,950
Forever buried in the dust

994
00:55:38,950 --> 00:55:39,910
Is Qin back?

995
00:55:39,910 --> 00:55:40,670
He's been back

996
00:55:40,670 --> 00:55:41,470
for many days.

997
00:55:43,030 --> 00:55:44,150
I have a surprise for you.

998
00:55:44,150 --> 00:55:45,270
What surprise?

999
00:55:45,510 --> 00:55:46,710
- A guy you want to see. - Who?

1000
00:55:46,870 --> 00:55:50,150
♪ On the horizon, you drift ♪

1001
00:55:51,310 --> 00:55:54,110
♪ Beyond white clouds ♪

1002
00:56:00,270 --> 00:56:03,750
♪ Ocean of misery ♪

1003
00:56:03,830 --> 00:56:07,750
♪ Stirring up love and hate ♪

1004
00:56:08,270 --> 00:56:12,350
♪ In this world ♪

1005
00:56:12,470 --> 00:56:16,550
♪ Fate is hard to escape ♪

1006
00:56:17,110 --> 00:56:20,270
♪ Deep in love ♪

1007
00:56:20,430 --> 00:56:24,750
♪ Yet we can't approach each other ♪
